<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN332-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – tumpai; tuṟai – vallāṇmullai. viriyūrnakkaṉār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN332">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>piṟarvēl pōlā tāki yivvūr</l>
<l>maṟavaṉ vēlō peruntakai yuṭaittē</l>
<l>yirumpuṟa nīṟu māṭik kalantiṭaik</l>
<l>kurampaik kūraik kiṭakkiṉuṅ kiṭakku</l>
<l>maṅkala makaḷiroṭu mālai cūṭṭi</l>
<l>yiṉkura lirumpai yāḻoṭu tatumpat</l>
<l>teṇṇīrp paṭuviṉun teruviṉun tirintu</l>
<l>maṇmuḻu taḻuṅkac celliṉuñ cellumāṅ</l>
<l>kiruṅkaṭaṟ ṟāṉai vēntar</l>
<l>peruṅkaḷiṟṟu mukattiṉuñ celavā ṉātē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Being unlike the spears of others, as for the spear </l>
<l>of the bold man from this village, it possesses great befittingness. (1f.)</l>
<l corresp="3">Bathing [its] large back in ashes(?), mingling in between, </l>
<l corresp="4">even if it lies, it will lie under the roof of a hut, </l>
<l corresp="5">and, being adorned with garlands by auspicious women, </l>
<l corresp="6">while sweet voices resound along with the lute in a large bag, </l>
<l corresp="7">wandering from clear-watered wells to streets, </l>
<l corresp="8">even if it goes it will go so that the whole earth is laid waste, and thus </l>
<l corresp="10">it won’t end in going into the face of the large elephant bull </l>
<l corresp="9">of kings with armies [like] the vast ocean. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
